<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-081-706  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 081 706.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  Feb 9 1989 v37 n3 p43(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Imaging chip holds three 15-MHz 8-bit ADCs. (triple flash analogto digital convertor for television) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goodenough, Frank.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Brooktree Corp offers two host-controllable analog-to-digitalconverter systems incorporated on a single chip.andP;  They are thefirst products of their type and are aimed at designers of videoimaging systems.andP;  The Bt251, for monochrome imaging, contains an8-bit flash analog-to-digital converter that samples video signalsbeyond 6 MHz at more than 15 mega-samples per second as well as a256-by-eight-bit RAM lookup table.andP;  The color Bt256 has three8-bit flash converters, making it possible to grab red, green andblue video signals simultaneously.andP;  Output-performance logic letsthe developer select 24-, 15-, or 8-bit true-color or 8-bitpseudo-color data formats.andP;  Both chips include a number of designtools to reduce board size, power consumption and productdevelopment time.andP;  On-chip features include input multiplexers,synchronization strippers, and dc-restoration circuits, all underhost-processor control.andP;  These products are designed for imagingapplications but engineers designing multichannel, high-speeddata-acquisition systems will also find them useful.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Brooktree Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Brooktree Bt251 (Digitizer) (product introduction)Brooktree Bt253 (Digitizer) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     New TechniqueAnalog to Digital ConvertorsVideo SystemsImaging TechnologyComputer-aided designComputer-aided engineeringData Acquisition SystemsNew ProductSemiconductors.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   8-bit, 15-MHz ADC with lookup table. (chart)Triple 8-bit, 15-MHz flash ADC. (chart)BT251 and BT253 specifications. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>